  "prompt": "How is energy engineering in the IITB?",
  "response": "IIT Bombay (IITB) is known for having a strong engineering program, including energy engineering. Here are some key points about energy engineering at IITB:\n\n1. Department Structure\n- Energy engineering is typically part of the Mechanical Engineering Department\n- Offers specialized courses and research opportunities in energy systems\n\n2. Academic Program\n- Undergraduate and postgraduate courses in energy engineering\n- Covers areas like renewable energy, thermal systems, energy efficiency\n- Curriculum includes both theoretical and practical components\n\n3. Research Focus\n- Strong emphasis on sustainable energy technologies\n- Research areas include solar energy, wind power, energy storage\n- Collaboration with industry and international research institutions\n\n4. Facilities\n- Advanced laboratories for energy systems research\n- State-of-the-art equipment and computational resources\n- Opportunities for hands-on projects and experiments\n\n5. Industry Connections\n- Internship opportunities with energy companies\n- Industry-sponsored research projects\n- Guest lectures from energy sector professionals\n\n6. Career Opportunities\n- Good placement record in energy sector companies\n- Opportunities in renewable energy, power generation, consulting firms\n\nFor the most current and specific details, I recommend contacting the IITB Mechanical Engineering Department directly.",
